<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910104-0060</DOCNO><DOCID>910104-0060.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Dollar General Corp.:   Tennessee Discount Chain   Cuts 47 Non-Retail Positions</HL><DATE>01/04/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   DOLR</CO><IN>BROADLINE RETAILERS, DEPARTMENT STORES (RTB)</IN><LP>   Dollar General Corp., saying it has streamlined workoperations, laid off 47 non-retail employees in Scottsville,Ky., and Nashville, Tenn.   More than half of the layoffs were made because thediscount chain closed its Scottsville-based store fixturerefurbishing facility. The work will now be done by twooutside contractors.</LP><TEXT>   The Nashville-based company said it plans no further staffreductions. Although the layoffs were &quot;painful,&quot; saidchairman and chief executive officer Cal Turner Jr., &quot;ourmanagement team is committed to the effective management ofoverhead which allows us to maintain our everyday low pricesfor our customers.&quot;</TEXT></DOC>